FBIS3-37247 "drsov031_a_94030" FBIS-SOV-94-031 Document Type:Daily Report 15 Feb 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Naumann Lays Wreath PM1502113594 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 15 Feb 94 p 3 PM1502113594 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Unattributed report: "Meeting at Russian Defense Ministry"] [Text] General Klaus Naumann, Bundeswehr general inspector, arrived in Russia on an official visit 14 February. On the same day he had a meeting with Army General Pavel Grachev, Russian defense minister. During the conversation they discussed a broad range of problems of pan-European security in the light of the worsening situation in the former Yugoslavia, along with questions of the peacekeeping activity of Russia and its Armed Forces and the prospects for the development of German-Russian cooperation, including military cooperation. The Bundeswehr general inspector also met with Andrey Kokoshin, Russian first deputy defense minister, and Colonel General Mikhail Kolesnikov, chief of the General Staff of the Russian Federation Armed Forces. The German guest laid a wreath on the Tomb of the Unknown Soldier at the Kremlin Wall.
